criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Individuals aged 18 and above;

          2. Subjects who are mentally capable to participate in the study and provide informed
             consent;

          3. Subjects who can communicate in Chinese or English;

          4. Subjects who are ambulatory and do not have difficulties travelling to the clinics for
             follow-up;

          5. Subjects who do not have plans to leave Hong Kong in the subsequent two years after
             recruitment; and

          6. Subjects who agree to give informed consent voluntarily.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Subjects who are unable to receive oral fluids;

          2. Subjects who have received surgery involving the intestine within past 30 days;

          3. Subjects who are pregnant or breastfeeding; and

          4. Subjects who are immunocompromised, e.g. on cancer treatment, bone marrow/organ
             transplant, immune deficiency, poorly controlled HIV/AIDS.
